transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra Quinn speaking.

Speaker 2: How can I help you?

Speaker 1: Yes, this is Alfred Shoshani.

Speaker 2: I ordered from you guys back in December,

Speaker 1: and I just received another shipment, which I never requested.

Speaker 2: And so I like, I don't know why you guys keep on sending this to me.

Speaker 1: So can you look it up and let me know what I need to do?

Speaker 2: What's your zip code?

Speaker 1: Hello? Zip code is 90049.

Speaker 2: What's your first and last name?

Speaker 1: First name is Fred, F-R-E-D.

Speaker 2: Last name is S-H-O-S-H-A-N-I.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Do you need the address?

Speaker 1: No. So your order does have refills, but you can choose when you get them.

Speaker 2: And you just have to set that up with your first purchase, whether you want it as needed

Speaker 1: or, you know, let us know when you want your orders to come out.

Speaker 2: If you don't do that, it will kind of come out this way, how the doctor writes it.

Speaker 1: Okay. You can go ahead and cancel the refill.

Speaker 2: So I don't need them anymore.

Speaker 1: So you don't want to order as needed?

Speaker 2: No.

Speaker 1: Okay. And you do understand that your prescription will be canceled

Speaker 2: and you won't be able to reorder, right?

Speaker 1: Oh, no. So go ahead, put me on as needed.

Speaker 2: So if I need it, I can call you guys back.

Speaker 1: Correct. Yes.

Speaker 2: So we'll just make your prescription available for you.

Speaker 1: Okay. All right.

Speaker 2: We'll do that for you now, sir.

Speaker 1: I do appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Anything else you need?

Speaker 1: That should do it, sir.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.

Speaker 1: Have a great day.

Speaker 2: You too, sir.

Speaker 1: All right. Bye.
